description: Associates the specified subnets and transit gateway attachments with the specified transit gateway multicast domain. The transit gateway attachment must be in the available state before you can add a resource. Use DescribeTransitGatewayAttachments to see the state of the attachment.

parameters.name: TransitGatewayMulticastDomainId
parameters.description: The ID of the transit gateway multicast domain.

parameters.name: TransitGatewayAttachmentId
parameters.description: The ID of the transit gateway attachment to associate with the transit gateway multicast domain.

parameters.name: SubnetIds
parameters.description: The IDs of the subnets to associate with the transit gateway multicast domain. (string) ---

nested_items.name: Associations
nested_items.description: Information about the transit gateway multicast domain associations.

nested_items.name: TransitGatewayAttachmentId

nested_items.name: ResourceType
nested_items.description: The type of resource, for example a VPC attachment.

nested_items.name: ResourceOwnerId
nested_items.description: The ID of the Amazon Web Services account that owns the resource.

nested_items.name: Subnets
nested_items.description: The subnets associated with the multicast domain.

nested_items.name: State
nested_items.description: The state of the subnet association.
